                <h1>Activating Background Knowledge: Tameka’s Effective Strategy</h1>
                <p>Tameka uses the strategy of activating background knowledge when introducing a new concept in her classroom. By prompting students to recall prior experiences or knowledge related to the topic, she fosters connections and enhances understanding. This approach is especially effective in subjects where critical thinking and personal relevance are key.</p>
